P_naPmdhm_KSYjUQp05RWhoqhH2jwrvjRnsvPwEOKGsJUwX3hg9qVFv9u4aMNvYmyUpyA_AsbwB_ZGSu-9UQjDDkx4OP1kfao512yJjDTiw5pCYNIRqX7A0_cT10cYEziP5nP_qoO8AMV99YaYp0hN48n_ORvUQizCZA==\",\"summary\":[{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Evaluating test setup and dependencies**\\n\\nI need to check class constants for native properties and refer to the Netty docs. An existing test may be enough, but I should be cautious about the actions I take. There’s a mention of optional OAuth2 requiring a dependency, but external remote endpoints can be flaky. The main guidance suggests no action is needed unless extra setup appears necessary. However, there might be a need for an optional Maven dependency if tests use OAuth2WebClient. I’m pondering how to approach this carefully.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Analyzing optional dependencies**\\n\\nThe artifact POM has an optional dependency for vertx-auth-oauth2. I’m wondering if code can compile without this optional dependency when using OAuth2Auth in the signature. The `vertx-web-client` jar has the OAuth2WebClient class, which references the optional dependency in its code. Since Maven's optional dependencies aren’t transitive, the test project needs to include it to avoid compile failures. However, if OAuth2Auth isn't directly referenced, I might compile without it. I think existing tests avoid OAuth2, so meaningful coverage should be reachable without this extra dependency.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Considering jackson-databind usage**\\n\\nI see that the POM for tests excludes jackson-databind as optional for some tests. I'm noticing that existing tests use BodyCodec.jsonObject and seem to succeed without it. Since Vert.x core depends on jackson-core, using JsonObject might not have issues with databind being optional. I think it’s not necessary to include the optional dependency after all, as the tests are working fine without it. I'll keep that in mind!\"}]}"}, {"type": "text", "text": "{\n  \"action\": \"advisory_preparation\",\n  \"summary\": \"No extra dependency or Docker service is needed: Vert.x Web Client can be meaningfully exercised against an in-process Vert.x HTTP server. However, vertx-web-client 5.0.1 resolves Vert.x Core with Netty 4.2.2.Final, and the existing 5.0.0 test already documents that Netty 4.2.x needs explicit unsafe-access runtime properties on Java 25 native runs.\",\n  \"deterministic_setup\": [],\n  \"agent_guidance\": \"For native test runtime on JDK 25/GraalVM, set runtime system properties equivalent to -Dsun.misc.unsafe.memory.access=allow and -Dio.netty.tryReflectionSetAccessible=true. Prefer local loopback HTTP-server tests using Vertx.createHttpServer() plus WebClient/WebClientSession/CachingWebClient; avoid remote network dependencies. Do not exercise OAuth2WebClient unless the test also adds the optional io.vertx:vertx-auth-oauth2 dependency intentionally.\",\n  \"risks\": [\n    \"The failing issue is for native-image runtime, so local Gradle/native-image verification remains necessary to confirm the Netty Java 25 properties are sufficient for 5.0.1.\",\n    \"OAuth2WebClient references optional Vert.x OAuth2 APIs; generated tests that import or instantiate it without adding the optional dependency may fail to compile.\",\n    \"External HTTP endpoints would make coverage flaky; use an in-process Vert.x server instead.\"\n  ]\n}", "textSignature": "{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_06a6f111f421d25f016a41ce194eb08194a61a88103803baa6\",\"phase\":\"final_answer\"}"}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "oca/gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 5824, "output": 835, "cacheRead": 20992, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 27651, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "stop", "timestamp": 1782697485516, "responseId": "resp_06a6f111f421d25f016a41ce0e23488194bbd084519ab0ff57"}, "toolResults": []}
